          <title>PROGRESS NOTES</title>
          <text>
            <table xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
              <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Provider</th><th>Note Type</th><th>Note Text</th><th>Location</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>03/18/2026</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: Cirrhosis follow-up, hepatology co-management.
HPI: 58yo male with alcoholic cirrhosis (Child-Pugh B, MELD 16). Sober since June 2024 on naltrexone. Reports compliance with lactulose -- 2-3 BMs daily, no confusion episodes since January admission. Abdomen: moderate ascites, last paracentesis 02/2026 (3L removed). Weight 185 (down from 192 after para). No melena, hematemesis. Eating better -- sees nutritionist monthly.
PE: Jaundice mild. Spider angiomata on chest. Abdomen: distended, fluid wave present, nontender. No asterixis. Oriented x3. Extremities: 1+ pretibial edema.
Assessment:
# Cirrhosis (K70.30): Child-Pugh B (score 8). MELD 16. Continue diuretics. Hepatology transplant evaluation in progress.
# Ascites (R18.8): Moderate. Sodium restriction &lt;2g/day. May need paracentesis in 4 weeks.
# HE (K72.90): Stable on lactulose + rifaximin. No episodes x 2 months.
# Varices (I85.00): EGD 09/2024 showed grade II. Nadolol for prophylaxis. Repeat EGD due 09/2026.
# AUD (F10.21): 21 months sober. Continue naltrexone, AA, therapy.
# Malnutrition: Albumin 2.8. High-protein diet. Nutritionist.
# HCC surveillance: AFP 8.2 normal. Liver US q6 months -- due 06/2026.
Plan: Continue all meds. Paracentesis if symptomatic. Hepatology transplant eval. Liver US 06/2026. Labs monthly. Return 4 weeks.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </text>
        </section>
